extends _base

include _index

block head
	title About us | Gripeless — Encourage complaining
	+landing-head
	+display-font

block body
	.font-display
		.mb-16
			+nav

		.mx-4.mb-16: .max-w-screen-md.mx-auto.text-lg
			h1.font-bold.text-xl.mb-2 About us
			p.mb-2.
				The goal behind our company has been and always will be product
				improvement. We want to see more great products out there
				that are reliable, predictable, and simply joyful to use.

			p.mb-2.
				We value software quality a lot, and seeing our customers fix
				problems with their products is incredibly satisfying. Whether
				it's clustered UI becoming clear, sluggish loading speeds
				becoming fast or just random bugs becoming squashed it always
				gives us a nice hit of dopamine and motivates us to keep going
				further.

			p.mb-4.
				We're seeking out to push software technology forward into the
				direction of "just working", and not just some of the time, but
				all of the time.

			p.mb-4.
				While having a goal of creating a reliable product is not
				important short term, on a longer time scale it always pays
				off. I like bringing up
				#[a.text-red-700(href='https://pinboard.in' class="hover:text-red-900") pinboard.in]
				which is enjoying hundreds of thousands of dollars in annual
				revenue despite being built and maintained by a single person.
				The product is designed to be simple and last years which is
				paying off well.

			p.mb-4.
				Like them or not, Apple products are a fantastic example of
				this too. All products are built on the principle of "just
				works" and I won't have to bring up revenue numbers. They're
				made to be fantastic to use, reliable and robust and that's
				why the company was able to get big.

			p.mb-4.
				We understand that the economical pressure to make your product
				robust right now looks low. It won't make or break your business
				whether your users experience one or two breaking bugs a day
				rather than zero since they're used to this experience from
				already using computers. But looking at Pinboard or Apple you
				can definitely make your product shine, stand out and
				ultimately rack you in some good profits.

			p.mb-4.
				And we really want to help you achieve that.

			hr.mb-4

			p.mb-2.
				Also, we really like talking about things like UX, front end
				performance, alternative programming languages and similar
				topics. A side goal of Gripeless is to explore some cutting
				edge ideas in programming that help us quickly iterate over
				the code without worrying that it's going to break somewhere.
				If your interests are
				shared, feel free to #[a.text-red-700(href='mailto:maciej@usegripeless.com' class="hover:text-red-900") contact me], I would really love to have a chat!
			p.text-base - Maciej, Gripeless Founder

		+foot

	+landing-script
